        "inline_data": null,
        "text": "I have successfully implemented the `logic-api` module according to the requirements.\n\n1. **Database & Polling**: Implemented `src/db.py` with SQLAlchemy and a `tenacity` polling loop (`wait_for_db`) that attempts to connect to PostgreSQL every 2 seconds (up to 10 attempts).\n2. **Data Fetching**: Implemented `src/data_fetcher.py` to fetch the last 730 days of historical data for the specified pairs (`DFAC/^GSPC`, `DXIV/URTH`, `DFAE/EEM`) using `yfinance`.\n3. **Logic**: Implemented `src/logic.py` to calculate the daily premium (`DFA_Daily_Return - Benchmark_Daily_Return`) rounded to 4 decimal places.\n4. **API Endpoints**: Implemented `src/main.py` with FastAPI, exposing `GET /health` and `GET /api/heatmap` with the exact required JSON schemas. The database initialization and data fetching are triggered on the first boot before the port is bound.\n5. **Testing**: All provided tests in `tests/test_api.py` and `tests/test_logic.py` pass successfully using a local SQLite database for testing isolation.\n\nThe state has been advanced to `QA_REVIEW`.",
